The Amazon Food Reviews Sentiment Analysis project leverages Natural Language Processing (NLP) techniques to analyze consumer sentiment in a dataset of 568,000 reviews. Hereâ€™s a detailed breakdown of the project:

Project: Amazon Food Reviews Sentiment Analysis
Objective:
To classify food reviews from Amazon into positive or negative sentiments using NLP and machine learning.

Dataset Details:

568,000 rows of data with review text and associated sentiment labels.
Key Steps:

Data Preprocessing:
Cleaning text data by removing stopwords, punctuation, and irrelevant characters.
Tokenization to split text into words.
Feature Extraction:
Used TF-IDF vectorization to represent text as numerical features for machine learning models.
Model Building:
Implemented machine learning algorithms (e.g., Naive Bayes, Logistic Regression) for sentiment classification.
Evaluation:
Evaluated model performance using metrics like accuracy, precision, recall, and F1-score.
Technologies Used:

Python Libraries: NLTK, Scikit-learn, Pandas, NumPy, Matplotlib, Seaborn.
Outcomes:

Achieved high accuracy in classifying sentiments, providing valuable insights into consumer opinions.
Enabled businesses to identify trends and areas for improvement based on customer feedback.
